Hi Marc,

I was curious if CUJ is interested in articles about Artificial Intelligence 
methods, in particular, best-first heuristic search of a problem state-space.
Since last summer I've been learning about AI, and I believe that your
readers may be interested in a templatized best-first search that I wrote
while learning about AI. The search routine is based on the algorithm
described in two books: Principles of Artificial Intelligence, by
Nils Nilsson, and Heuristics: Intelligent Search Strategies for Computer
Problem Solving by J. Pearl (the bible for heuristic search methods).

The code was tested with several of the "classic" AI problems: N-queens,
missionary-cannibals, eight-cube, and a coins problem which may not be
so "classic."

Please let me know if there is any interest. Thank you !!!

Mike Rumore
mrumore@lucent.com



