Hi Mike,

We definitely are interested. The problem I've seen with AI type
articles (e.g., articles describing genetic algorithms) is that the
author focuses so much on describing how the algorithm works that he
doesn't give the reader a clue as to how to adapt his/her problem to the
code. So the example or examples you give should clearly illustrate the
process by which a user "hooks" his/her problem into the code. You
should also probably say a little bit about what kinds of problems are
appropriate and what kinds are best suited to other approaches.

I would like to see an article of around 2500 to 3000 words. I'd like to
receive a draft by the end of February. BTW -- I am assuming Lucent has
no ownership issues with this code?

Marc


